# Debugging
- Always use `throw new Error()` with descriptive messages for debugging
- Go straight to the point - no placeholder errors or console.error
- Fix issues immediately, don't mask them

# Testing
- Mock dependencies OR ensure database is seeded before tests
- Each test must have its own seeded data
- Verify data exists before running assertions
- Check Makefile for available commands and contexts

# Project Tools
- Reference Makefile for all available commands and contexts